### ============================================================================
### E2E SYSTEM TEST SUITE
### Update these 3 variables ONLY AFTER running Step 2
### ============================================================================
@ambulanceId = b9399a72-a368-4f7d-802b-651a4f032bc7
@emergencyId = 0024c66f-42be-4a9b-a814-72a217b0e0a1
@hospitalId = 7bbd1da5-26d4-4f80-a419-49e7e4d50386

@emergencyHost = http://localhost:8082
@ambulanceHost = http://localhost:8083
@locationHost = http://localhost:8084
@hospitalHost = http://localhost:8086

### ============================================================================
### PHASE 1: PRE-FLIGHT CHECKS (Run these to verify system state before disaster)
### ============================================================================

### 1A. Check Available Ambulances (Note how many are AVAILABLE)
GET {{ambulanceHost}}/ambulances
Accept: application/json

### 1B. Check Available Hospitals (Note the bed count at AIIMS)
GET {{hospitalHost}}/hospitals?minBeds=1
Accept: application/json


### ============================================================================
### PHASE 2: THE CATALYST (The Event-Driven Entry Point)
### ============================================================================

### 2. Create Emergency
# -> Hits the Emergency Service (8082)
# -> Publishes to Kafka (emergency-events)
# -> Matching Service consumes it and triggers the Saga!
POST {{emergencyHost}}/emergency
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "Patient-007",
  "severity": "CRITICAL",
  "latitude": 20.29,
  "longitude": 85.81
}

### ============================================================================
### PHASE 3: PARAMEDIC HANDOFF (Manual field actions)
### ============================================================================

### 3A. Verify Ambulance is now RESERVED (Automatic from Saga)
GET {{ambulanceHost}}/ambulances
Accept: application/json

### 3B. Paramedic Action: Patient Picked Up (Changes to IN_TRANSIT)
POST {{ambulanceHost}}/ambulances/{{ambulanceId}}/pickup/{{emergencyId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 3C. Paramedic Action: Patient Delivered (Changes to AVAILABLE)
POST {{ambulanceHost}}/ambulances/{{ambulanceId}}/deliver/{{emergencyId}}/{{hospitalId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 3D. Check Hospital Beds (Verify the bed was actually consumed/updated)
GET {{hospitalHost}}/hospitals
Accept: application/json